%% OBJECTIVE: Ensure the change management process meets SOX audit requirements by embedding mandatory compliance checkpoints, role accountability via RACI labels, and documentation gates that prevent changes from progressing without proper evidence and authorization.
%%
%% EXPLANATION:
%% Added four documentation gates (business justification, impact analysis/test evidence, implementation/backout plans, and post-implementation evidence package) as parallelogram-shaped nodes with completion loops. Inserted three SOX compliance control checkpoints (segregation of duties, approval authorization, and audit trail review) as hexagonal decision nodes with remediation loops for failures. Labeled all process steps with RACI roles (Change Manager, Change Owner, CAB Chair, Technical Team, Compliance Officer) indicating Responsible, Accountable, Consulted, or Informed designations. Added a RACI legend subgraph for reference. Rerouted the incident report path through the final SOX audit trail review to ensure failed changes also undergo compliance verification before closure.
